 "overview": "\u003Cp\u003EGet \u0026#8220;Liked\u0026#8221; for your free Wi-Fi. Local merchants can turn patrons into Facebook fans in return for giving them free Wi-Fi.\u003C/p\u003E\n\n\u003Cp\u003EMany local merchants have discovered the value of \u003Cem\u003EFacebook fan pages\u003C/em\u003E as a marketing tool, just like the major brands. It enables interaction, social recommendations to their fan\u0026#8217;s friends, ease-of-use, and range of rich media. Similarly, merchants are paying \u0026#8220;Daily Deal\u0026#8221; sites lots of money to bring them new\ncustomers \u0026#8211; and want to break the cycle of paying again to bring them back. Signage and in-store promotions have limited effectiveness to get patrons to \u0026#8220;like\u0026#8221; the merchant on Facebook, in order to build a relationship. \u003C/p\u003E\n\n\u003Cp\u003EWith more patrons carrying smartphones, tablets, and laptops, there is greater demand for free Wi-Fi while waiting for service, to check for messages, or to\npass the time. While some can access 3G wireless, they prefer local Wi-Fi because of faster speeds, better coverage, and no data caps. \u003C/p\u003E\n\n\u003Cp\u003EWavespot enables the merchants to offer free Wi-Fi, and asks that patrons \u0026#8220;like\u0026#8221; the merchant on Facebook in return. That \u0026#8220;like\u0026#8221; appears on the patron\u0026#8217;s wall as a social recommendation. And the \u0026#8220;like\u0026#8221; creates a new fan for ongoing marketing.\u003C/p\u003E",
